The Priscilla
Warm ginger and spices with a molasses sweetness
signature
Spiced, Sweet, Soft

INGREDIENTS:
2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour
3/4 cup butter
1 1/4 cups brown sugar
1/4 cup molasses
2 eggs
1 tbsp baking soda
1 tbsp vanilla extract
1 tbsp ginger
1/2 tbsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp allspice
1/2 tsp cloves

INSTRUCTIONS:
Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
Beat butter and brown sugar with mixer until smooth and fluffy. Add eggs, molasses and vanilla; beat until well blended
Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices; beat until combined
Form tablespoon-sized dough balls and coat in cinnamon-sugar mix. Place 2in apart on sheet
Bake just until cookies lose their shiny appearance, about 12 minutes
Let cookies cool for 10 minutes before removing. Makes 40-50 cookies